you to stop, Nico Robin.

225
00:20:07,574 --> 00:20:10,644
Hey! Are you listening to me?

226
00:20:10,677 --> 00:20:13,246
Don't forget
who's the boss here!

227
00:20:13,513 --> 00:20:15,449
Alright, Lucci. Just drag her!

228
00:20:15,482 --> 00:20:22,122
Pull her by the hair
if you have to!

229
00:20:22,155 --> 00:20:24,625
It's an order. Now come on.

230
00:20:24,658 --> 00:20:26,393
Start walking.

231
00:20:28,562 --> 00:20:30,497
You're delusional, aren't you?

232
00:20:30,530 --> 00:20:33,334
Oh, my. You're honestly
convinced that the Straw Hats

233
00:20:33,367 --> 00:20:38,672
are still on their way
to rescue you. Moron!

234
00:20:38,705 --> 00:20:41,275
I've never seen such
a weak-looking pirate crew.

235
00:20:41,308 --> 00:20:44,078
If that's your only hope,
that's pretty sad.

236
00:20:44,111 --> 00:20:45,379
That explosion we heard earlier

237
00:20:45,412 --> 00:20:47,414
was probably the
pipes or something.

238
00:20:47,447 --> 00:20:49,717
There's no way they
could make it this far!

239
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,652
While you're off in your
little fantasy world,

240
00:20:51,685 --> 00:20:53,320
dreaming of being rescued,

241
00:20:53,353 --> 00:20:55,422
we'll pass the Gates of Justice.

242
00:20:55,455 --> 00:20:58,259
The Bridge of
Hesitation lies right

243
00:20:58,292 --> 00:21:00,160
before the Gates of Justice.

244
00:21:00,193 --> 00:21:03,097
We'll cross the first
elevated half of the bridge.

245
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:05,499
And once the gates
are within our sight,

246
00:21:05,532 --> 00:21:08,569
the other half of the bridge
will rise from the sea.

247
00:21:08,602 --> 00:21:12,106
And then we'll finally pass
through the gates themselves.

248
00:21:12,139 --> 00:21:14,341
Once the gates have
firmly closed behind us,

249
00:21:14,374 --> 00:21:16,510
every lingering trace
of your pathetic,

250
00:21:16,543 --> 00:21:20,314
misguided optimism will
be dashed to pieces.

251
00:21:20,347 --> 00:21:22,650
You'll forget what
hope even means.

252
00:21:22,683 --> 00:21:24,685
The only feeling left
in your body will be

253
00:21:24,718 --> 00:21:27,588
an overwhelming and
eternal sense of guilt.

254
00:21:27,621 --> 00:21:30,224
You will spend your days
in ceaseless atonement

255
00:21:30,257 --> 00:21:32,426
for your arrogant
crime of existing.

256
00:21:32,459 --> 00:21:36,129
You know it's true. Nico Robin.

257
00:21:56,350 --> 00:21:58,485
Now then. Hurry along.

258
00:21:58,518 --> 00:22:01,054
Move your feet, wench!

259
00:22:05,425 --> 00:22:15,402
Robin! Robin! Robin!

260
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:23,210
Wh-wh-what was that?

261
00:22:23,243 --> 00:22:25,179
I heard someone!
Did you hear that?

262
00:22:25,212 --> 00:22:26,680
Who was it?

263
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:31,685
You better take
Nico Robin and start moving.

264
00:22:31,718 --> 00:22:34,187
Don't worry, chief,
I'll handle this.

265
00:22:37,291 --> 00:22:38,492
A door!

266
00:22:38,526 --> 00:22:42,562
At least it doesn't look like
it's made of iron this time.

267
00:22:54,374 --> 00:22:59,346
It's big in here. Where am I?

268
00:22:59,379 --> 00:23:02,315
I found you, Pigeon-bastard.

269
00:23:04,251 --> 00:23:06,620
Glad you could make it.

270
00:23:13,193 --> 00:23:15,562
Hey! Answer me! CP9!

271
00:23:15,595 --> 00:23:17,731
One of the pirates caught
up with us somehow.

272
00:23:17,764 --> 00:23:20,434
Come on! Are you even
listening to me?

273
00:23:20,467 --> 00:23:21,569
Wait! No!

274
00:23:21,602 --> 00:23:22,803
Look at what you're holding!

275
00:23:22,836 --> 00:23:23,971
What?

276
00:23:24,004 --> 00:23:28,742
I pressed the button on the
golden transponder snail!

277
00:23:29,009 --> 00:23:30,477
On the next One Piece:

278
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:34,114
"Resounding Bad News!
Buster Call Invoked!"

279
00:23:34,147 --> 00:23:36,516
I'm gonna be
King of the Pirates!

